    "body": "### Description\n\nHi, \nwhen i accept a completion after the call to `require'lspconfig'.rust_analyzer.setup {` it overwrites the following word, even though I have set `[\"<CR>\"] = cmp.mapping.confirm({behaviour = cmp.ConfirmBehavior.Insert}),\n` in the \n```\nlocal cmp = require(\"cmp\")\ncmp.setup({\n  mapping = {\n    [\"<CR>\"] = cmp.mapping.confirm({behaviour = cmp.ConfirmBehavior.Insert})\n```\n\n## Dirty fix:\nadd an `entry_filter` to the `nvim_lsp` source\n```lua\nlocal modify_text_edit = function(entry, ctx)\n    local item = entry:get_completion_item()\n    if item.textEdit and item.textEdit.range then\n        local range = item.textEdit.range\n        -- I dont exactly know why I want this on_same_line requirement\n        local on_same_line = range.start.line == range[\"end\"].line\n        if on_same_line then\n            -- this ensures that no text is replaced\n            item.textEdit.range[\"end\"].character = item.textEdit.range.start.character\n            entry.completion_item = item\n        end\n    end\n    return true\nend\n```\nand \n```lua\ncmp.setup({\n    mapping = {\n        [\"<CR>\"] = cmp.mapping.confirm({behaviour = cmp.ConfirmBehavior.Insert}),\n    },\n    sources =  {\n        { name = 'nvim_lsp', entry_filter = modify_text_edit},\n```",
